Maybe keeping it in 4D throughout would save some computation time. Because every reshape operation involves copying data, which takes time.

So, perhaps modifying the code to avoid reshaping as much as possible. Instead of reshaping to 2D, apply LayerNorm directly on the channel dimension while keeping the spatial dimensions as 1x1.

Wait, LayerNorm expects input in (batch_size, features,...) format. So if the input after gavg is (batch_size, channels, 1, 1), then the features are along the second dimension. So applying LayerNorm over the channels should work without reshaping.

Yes! That makes sense. So instead of reshaping to 2D, just apply LayerNorm on the channel dimension. This would eliminate two reshape operations, which should speed things up.

